Add this to your build.gradle:

    android {
        dexOptions {
            preDexLibraries = false
        }
    }

I suppose this way there is no conflicting `BuildConfig.java`.

**EDIT:**

Why the above works:
Android studio will first [dex][1] the libraries before dex-ing the app module. If you have a library module with the same package name as your app module, this &#39;pre-dexing&#39; will result in the creation of a `BuildConfig.java` in the same package as for the app.

Note: &#39;pre-dexing&#39; will [slow down your build process a bit][2] so I suggest that you change your library&#39;s package name instead. 

  [1]: https://stackoverflow.com/a/20757229/1773325
  [2]: http://google.github.io/android-gradle-dsl/current/com.android.build.gradle.internal.dsl.DexOptions.html#com.android.build.gradle.internal.dsl.DexOptions:preDexLibraries

